Let’s get one thing straight — if you’re skipping sunscreen, no amount of anti-aging serums or expensive skincare can truly save your skin.

UV rays are the #1 cause of premature aging — think fine lines, wrinkles, sun spots, and loss of elasticity. Even on cloudy days or while indoors, UVA rays can penetrate windows and break down collagen over time. That “glow” you’re chasing? Sunscreen is where it starts.

But I get it — most sunscreens feel heavy, greasy, or leave a white cast. That’s exactly why I swear by the Beauty of Joseon Relief Sun: Rice + Probiotics SPF50+.

Here’s why this one stands out:
• Lightweight & hydrating — feels more like a moisturizer than sunscreen
• No white cast — perfect for all skin tones
• Non-sticky & absorbs beautifully — plays well under makeup
• Rich in skin-loving ingredients like rice extract & probiotics to soothe, nourish, and strengthen the skin barrier
• Gives a natural, healthy glow without looking oily

It’s gentle, effective, and makes daily SPF actually enjoyable. If sunscreen always felt like a chore, this one might change your mind.

Daily SPF isn’t optional — it’s the foundation of truly healthy, youthful skin. Start now, and your future self will thank you.

The one step your skincare might be missing? A really good toner.

Toners often get overlooked, but they’re actually one of the most crucial steps in any routine — especially if you’re layering products. Think of it this way: skincare is all about absorption. The thinner the product, the deeper it penetrates. That’s why toner should always come right after cleansing — it preps your skin, balances its pH, and acts like a sponge to help everything you apply next work better.

I’ve been using the Round Lab Dokdo Toner, and I genuinely see why it’s so hyped. It’s enriched with Deep Sea Water from Ulleungdo, which is packed with minerals that help soothe, hydrate, and strengthen the skin barrier. Ingredients like panthenol and allantoin give it that calming, nourishing edge — perfect for sensitive or irritated skin.

It’s super lightweight, absorbs quickly, and leaves no sticky residue — just a soft, hydrated base that feels refreshed.

How I use it:
After cleansing, I pour a few drops into my palms and gently press it into my face (you can also use a cotton pad if you prefer). I sometimes do 2 layers when my skin feels extra thirsty.

If you’ve been skipping toner or using one that just doesn’t do much — trust me, this one’s worth a try. It’s gentle, effective, and makes a noticeable difference in how your skin drinks up the rest of your routine.

First shipping received.

“Okay so, Nykaa haul time!
I’ve been super mindful with my shopping lately… matlab, sale chal rahi thi, but I didn’t go crazy.
Mujhe kaafi time se kuch essentials chahiye the, and thankfully, yeh sab cheezein mujhe mil gayi — that too on discount!
Now here’s the trick — jab bhi sale ho, na, aisa kuch lo jo kabhi discount pe nahi aata and jo tum already soch rahe ho lene ka from a long time.
So I picked only those things jo actually kaam ki hain. Nothing random!

Agar tumhe kisi product ka detailed review chahiye, just comment below and I’ll make it!
Aur agar kisi ko link chahiye, woh bhi comment kar do — I’ll send it across!”
